            <h3 style="width: 99rem;">CSS Background Size and Background Repeat property</h3>

            <div class="explore">
              <p style="margin-top: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;">&#x2022; The background-size property sets the size of the
                element's background image. The image can be left to its natural size, stretched, or constrained to fit
                the available space.</p>
              <p style="margin-top: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;">&#x2022; The background-repeat property sets if/how a background image will be repeated. By default, a background-image is repeated both vertically and horizontally.</p>
              <p style="margin-top: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;">&#x2022; Generally, there are different values in background-repeat property like - no-repeat, repeat, repeat-x, repeat-y, initial, space, round, inherit etc. that you can try in your css code according to the condition.</p>

              <div id="ps-box" class="ps-box" style="margin: 2rem 0rem;">

                <p style="color: rgb(190, 190, 190);">selector{</p>
                <p style="color: rgb(190, 190, 190); margin-left: 4rem;">property: value;</p>
                <p style="color: rgb(190, 190, 190);">}</p>

              </div>

              <p style="margin-top: 1rem; margin-left: 1rem;">Here selector can be different tags like h1, p, div,
                table, span, classname, idname or more. Property will be
                background-size with background-repeat. The value of the background-size can be px, em, rem or other formats and background-repeat value will be no-repeat or other types.</p>
              
